                <div class="text-slate-700 flex-1">
                    <button type="button" @@click="open=!open" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 group">
                        <span class="badge pill-info">v2.23.0-pre.43</span>
                        <span class="text-xs text-brand-600 group-hover:underline">@T("SÃ¼rÃ¼m notlarÄ±", "Release notes") <i class="bi" :class="open ? 'bi-chevron-up' : 'bi-chevron-down'"></i></span>
                    </button>
                    <div x-show="open" x-cloak class="mt-3 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">
                        @if (en)
                        {
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.21.0 â€” Compliance pack (SIEM, encrypted backups, rate limiting)</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.21.0)</strong> SIEM/syslog forwarding of audit events (PCI 10.5.4); password-reuse prevention (PCI 8.3.7); AES-256 encrypted backups (PCI 3.x); per-IP rate limiting on login (NIST SC-5); and a security.txt (RFC 9116). All DB-agnostic, no structural changes.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.20.2 â€” Security headers &amp; password policy</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.20.2)</strong> A full Content-Security-Policy plus hardened security headers are now sent on every response (clickjacking/MIME/external-source restrictions). Configurable local password policy (min length + complexity), enforced at setup and on password change; local users can change their own password from My Profile. OWASP ASVS Â· PCI 8.3.6 Â· NIST 800-63B Â· SC-7.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.20.1 â€” Tamper-evident audit log</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.20.1)</strong> The audit log is now hash-chained (each entry includes the SHA-256 hash of the previous). A "Verify Integrity" button detects any modified or deleted entry. Works on every database. PCI DSS 10.3.x Â· NIST AU-9 Â· ISO 27001 A.8.15.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.20.0 â€” Regulatory compliance section</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.20.0)</strong> About now has a collapsible "Regulatory Compliance" section mapping vMon to PCI DSS / NIST / ISO 27001 / CIS / OWASP ASVS clauses with explanations (bilingual). Start of the compliance phase. Windows CPU now uses a processor-group-aware counter (fixes under-reporting on 64+ core servers).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.19.2 â€” Three-column Settings</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.19.2)</strong> Settings are now a single page in three balanced columns with the section menu removed â€” denser, gap-free. Functions unchanged.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.19.1 â€” Compact two-column Settings</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.19.1)</strong> Settings now use two independent balanced columns (no empty gaps), tighter/compact fields and cards, related settings grouped, single page with a sticky section menu. Nothing functional changed.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.19.0 â€” Settings fix &amp; chart/CPU tweaks</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.19.0) Settings:</strong> fixed a regression where only the first section showed. Rebuilt as a single page in a two-column layout with a sticky section menu that smooth-scrolls to each group. All settings &amp; functions intact.</li><li><strong>(2.19.0)</strong> Fleet/Capacity chart legends no longer overlap the axis. Windows CPU is now read twice (short interval) to avoid an occasional cold/low first reading.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.18.0 â€” Redesigned Settings &amp; EOL drill-down</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.18.0) Settings redesign:</strong> the long single column is now organised into tabs (Monitoring, Notifications, Access &amp; Login, Security, Data &amp; Backup, Other) with related settings grouped together and a sticky Save bar. No setting's function changed.</li><li><strong>(2.18.0)</strong> In Statistics, clicking an end-of-life OS row now lists exactly which servers run that version.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.17.0 â€” Real EOL via endoflife.date</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.17.0) End-of-life check:</strong> optional integration with endoflife.date for real OS support-end dates (past-EOL and "soon" warnings). Privacy-safe â€” your inventory never leaves; only public version tables are downloaded and matched locally, cached, refreshed weekly. Air-gapped sites can import the data as JSON. Falls back to the static list when disabled. Configure under Settings â†’ End-of-Life (EOL).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.16.0 â€” PDF report &amp; outage drill-down</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.16.0) Management report:</strong> a new "PDF Report" button opens a clean, branded, printable report (KPIs, OS distribution, fleet trend, top consumers, uptime, outages, EOL) â€” print or save as PDF for weekly/monthly reviews.</li><li><strong>(2.16.0)</strong> Outage summary bars are now clickable â€” click a day to see that day's outages (server, start/end, duration). Detail dialog headers no longer overlap rows when scrolling.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.15.3 â€” Build fix</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.15.3)</strong> Fixes the v2.15.2 release build (a missing using directive). Same content as 2.15.2.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.15.2 â€” Faster stats &amp; histogram drill-down</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.15.2) Performance:</strong> time-series indexes added, statistics aggregation pushed into the database (no longer loads raw rows), and the result is briefly cached â€” the Statistics (and Reports) pages open much faster. Same data, same features.</li><li><strong>(2.15.2)</strong> Click a bar in the Usage Distribution widget to see which servers fall in that band (e.g. 40-60% CPU).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.15.1 â€” Capacity CPU &amp; rising usage</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.15.1)</strong> The Capacity widget now has a CPU tab (used vs allocated cores) alongside RAM/Disk. New "Rising usage" widget lists servers whose CPU/RAM/Disk usage rose more than 10 points vs ~7 days ago.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.15.0 â€” Statistics insight pack</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.15.0)</strong> Nine new widgets: Fleet trend (30-day CPU/RAM/Disk), Top resource consumers, Critical (disk 85%+/threshold), Uptime (24h/7d), Usage histogram, Capacity used-vs-allocated, Outage summary, EOL OS, and a CPU heatmap. Resource cards now show a mini sparkline.</li><li><strong>(2.15.0)</strong> Page tools: fullscreen (NOC mode), last-updated time, summary CSV export, and a "reset to default layout" button (use it to get the new widgets on an existing dashboard).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.14.1 â€” Emails on sync</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.14.1)</strong> "Sync from LDAP" now also pulls each member's email â€” so all users' emails fill in at once, not only after they log in.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.14.0 â€” OTP safeguards &amp; LDAP email</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.14.0)</strong> LDAP logins now auto-fetch the user's email (AD <code>mail</code>) and store it â€” shown on the Users screen and used for email OTP.</li><li><strong>(2.14.0)</strong> Enabling OTP is now blocked unless at least one active admin has the contact (email/phone) for the selected channel â€” prevents locking everyone out.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.13.2 â€” Pie drill-down</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.13.2)</strong> Clicking a pie (or its center number) now opens a numeric category breakdown as bars (e.g. 95 Windows / 144 Linux); clicking a category drills into the matching servers, with a "back to categories" button.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.13.1 â€” Trend ranges</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.13.1)</strong> The detail dialog trend now has selectable ranges â€” 7 days / 1 month / 3 months / 6 months / 1 year â€” bucketed daily, weekly or monthly as the range grows. (Long ranges depend on the history retention setting.)</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.13.0 â€” Statistics polish</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.13.0)</strong> Statistics now sources everything from health-monitored servers only (Windows Health + Linux Health) â€” so "Total servers" and Up/Down/Error are correct and consistent.</li><li><strong>(2.13.0)</strong> Dark theme support on the Statistics page; pie tooltips no longer clipped (full name shows). Click any chart, counter or slice to open a detail dialog listing the matching servers and a 7-day trend for CPU/RAM/Disk.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.12.3 â€” Restore crash fix &amp; hardening</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.12.3) Critical fix:</strong> after restoring an older database, newly added required columns were left NULL, which crashed login and other pages ("data is NULL at ordinal N"). Startup now backfills those NULLs with safe defaults â€” existing data recovers automatically.</li><li><strong>(2.12.3) Security hardening:</strong> the file-based recovery (reset-admin / disable-auth) was removed. The error page no longer leaks exception details â€” it shows a generic message with a reference id; full detail goes to the logs only.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.12.2 â€” Recovery &amp; visible errors</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.12.2) Break-glass recovery:</strong> drop a <code>Data\reset-admin.txt</code> file containing <code>username|password</code> to (re)create a local admin and grant it admin rights on next start. Or drop <code>Data\disable-auth.txt</code> to temporarily turn off the login requirement (open mode) if login is broken. The file is consumed and deleted automatically.</li><li><strong>(2.12.2) Visible errors:</strong> the error page is no longer hidden behind the login redirect â€” unhandled errors are logged and their summary is shown, so problems are diagnosable instead of looking like "login does nothing".</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.12.1 â€” Local user lockout fix</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.12.1)</strong> LDAP sync no longer deactivates local users (e.g. the setup admin) â€” they are not tied to AD group membership. On startup any local user that was wrongly deactivated is reactivated automatically, so an existing locked install recovers on upgrade (no reinstall).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.12.0 â€” Statistics dashboard</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.12.0) Statistics tab:</strong> a new widget-based analytics board (Apache ECharts + Gridstack + CountUp). Counters, used-vs-allocated CPU/RAM/Disk, OS distribution (full version auto-detected on Windows &amp; Linux health checks), and Tag-based pie charts. Drag/resize is behind an edit-lock (like Zabbix); admins arrange the shared layout. Health checks now store structured CPU cores / RAM &amp; disk GB and the exact OS version.</li><li><strong>(2.12.0)</strong> "Keyword" is now called <strong>Tag</strong> (Etiket) across Services and Reports.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.11.1 â€” Large restore fix</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.11.1)</strong> Restoring a large database (e.g. 180&nbsp;MB) no longer fails with HTTP 400 â€” the upload limit was raised, and a new <em>restore from a server-side path</em> option was added (no upload limit, ideal for big files already on the server).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.11.0 â€” SQLite backup & restore</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.11.0) Backup &amp; restore:</strong> Settings now has a Backup section â€” pick a server-side folder, take a consistent (online) backup on demand, or schedule a daily one with retention. Restore from the list or upload a <code>.db</code> from another machine (used to migrate an old database). Works independently of any external DB tooling; SQLite only.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.10.0 â€” Two-factor login (OTP)</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.10.0) Two-step verification:</strong> after the password, an optional one-time code is required. Channel is configurable in Settings â€” <strong>Email (SMTP), SMS or WhatsApp</strong> â€” and the code is sent to the user's own email/phone (set in the new <em>My Profile</em> page). 6-digit code, 5-minute expiry, attempt-limited.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.9.2 â€” Service restart & cleaner startup</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.9.2)</strong> After setup, the app now restarts correctly in Windows Service mode (recovery-based). Startup no longer logs harmless EF errors (legacy blind ALTERs removed; schema handled by EnsureCreated + additive sync).</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.9.1 â€” Installer script fix</p><ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3"><li><strong>(2.9.1)</strong> Installer scripts are now ASCII-safe so they run on Windows PowerShell 5.1 regardless of file encoding.</li></ul><p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.9.0 â€” Installer & dual hosting</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.9.0) One-step install package:</strong> a self-contained release (no .NET needed on the target) with install / upgrade / uninstall scripts. Tagging a version builds the zip automatically.</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.9.0) IIS or Windows Service:</strong> the app can run either under IIS or as a Windows Service (Kestrel) â€” chosen by the installer. HTTPS handling is configurable for reverse-proxy setups.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.8.0 â€” UTC time handling</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.8.0) UTC storage / local display:</strong> all timestamps are stored in UTC and shown in your local time. This keeps reports and history consistent across servers and time zones (cloud-ready).</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.7.0 â€” Safe schema upgrades</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.7.0) Provider-independent schema sync:</strong> when a new version adds a column, it is added to the existing database automatically on any provider â€” additive only (never drops or alters), so there is no data-loss risk.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.6.0 â€” Multi-database & setup wizard</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.6.0) Multiple databases:</strong> SQLite, SQL Server, PostgreSQL, MySQL and Oracle are supported. The provider is chosen at install time; the DB can be local or on a separate server.</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.6.0) First-run setup wizard:</strong> on a fresh install the app asks for the database (with a connection test), company name, an admin account and SMTP (optional, with a test send).</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.6.0) Local admin login:</strong> a password-protected local admin is created during setup, so the app requires sign-in from the start. LDAP can be configured later and the local account removed.</li>
                                <li class="text-slate-500">Under the hood: a DB-external bootstrap layer, a secret-protection abstraction (DPAPI today, cloud/AES-ready) and a hardened startup that never errors on first run.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.5.4 â€” Translation pass 2</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.5.4) More English coverage:</strong> Dashboard edit, Service edit, Credential edit, Integration edit and Edit Permissions screens, the Reports table (types, durations, detail) and recurring Audit descriptions are now translated. The "(soon)" tag was removed from WhatsApp/Call (now live).</li>
                                <li class="text-slate-500">Note: native browser controls (file picker "Choose file", the date-time picker popup) follow the browser's own language and can't be forced from the app.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.5.3 â€” Wider translation & Voice/IVR merge</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.5.3) Translation:</strong> The Reconciliation page is now fully bilingual (server-side); remaining Turkish labels in Audit and Settings (LDAP / Security & Compliance / Notification Channels / Login logo) were translated.</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.5.3) Voice Call / IVR merged:</strong> The separate "Voice Call" channel type was merged into "IVR" as a single <b>"Voice Call / IVR"</b> option (both do the same job). Existing Voice integrations are migrated automatically.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.5.2 â€” About in English & fixes</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>(2.5.2) About fully English:</strong> The About page is now rendered server-side in the selected language. From now on every change is written in both Turkish and English.</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.5.2) Dark theme fix:</strong> The service status cards at the bottom of the dashboard are no longer white in dark mode.</li>
                                <li><strong>(2.5.2) WhatsApp template restored:</strong> The approved template (Content SID) field was added to the WhatsApp integration (Notification Channels). When set, alarms are sent as interactive button templates again; the previous template is restored automatically and can be changed any time.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.5.x â€” Language (TR/EN) & theme</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>Language selection:</strong> A <b>Language</b> option (Turkish ğŸ‡¹ğŸ‡· / English ğŸ‡¬ğŸ‡§) was added to the user menu; the choice is remembered per user and the UI is translated.</li>
                                <li><strong>Dark theme:</strong> Click your name (top right) â†’ <b>Theme</b> â†’ Light/Dark (a colour dot next to each). Remembered per user across logins and devices.</li>
                                <li><strong>Chart theming:</strong> Chart axis/grid colours follow the theme; UP/DOWN/ERROR/SLOW/TOTAL boxes are readable in dark mode.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.3.0 â€” Dashboard tabs merged</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li>The separate "Dashboard" menu item was removed. The main (unfiltered) view is now a fixed <b>"All"</b> first sub-tab inside "Dashboards"; it cannot be deleted or reordered.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.2.x â€” Notification Channels (single box)</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>One "Notification Channels" box:</strong> SMS / WhatsApp / Voice / IVR integrations are added, edited, deleted and toggled from one place in Settings. Pick the type when adding; each integration can use its own recipient list. No code changes needed.</li>
                                <li><strong>Flexible integration model:</strong> all channels use the same templated HTTP request (placeholders {to}/{from}/{message}/{user}/{password}/{apikey}). On an alarm, all active integrations matching the per-service switches (Mail/SMS/WhatsApp/Call) are triggered. The built-in Twilio settings were migrated into integrations automatically.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.1.x â€” Bulk edit & design</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>On/off switches:</strong> all active/passive checkboxes are now modern toggles (grey when off, green when on).</li>
                                <li><strong>Extended bulk edit:</strong> on Services, "Edit Selected" can change check interval, slowness threshold and CPU/RAM/Disk thresholds in bulk, and bulk-add keywords. On/off fields use segmented buttons (Keep/On/Off).</li>
                                <li><strong>Fix:</strong> when both Type and Keyword filters are chosen on a dashboard, their <b>intersection</b> is used.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 2.0.x â€” Interactive WhatsApp (Phase 4)</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>Templated alarm + buttons:</strong> alarms via an approved WhatsApp template ({{1}}..{{4}}) with Start / Restart / Stop buttons.</li>
                                <li><strong>Two-way control:</strong> pressing a button calls an inbound webhook that applies start/stop/restart to the related service; the result is replied over WhatsApp.</li>
                                <li><strong>Authorization & mapping:</strong> the phone number is mapped to a user (Phone field under Users); only users with the <b>"Manage alarms"</b> permission can act, others get a "no permission" reply. All actions are written to the Audit log.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 1.8â€“1.9 â€” SMS & WhatsApp notifications</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>SMS / WhatsApp notifications (Twilio):</strong> a message is sent when a service goes DOWN/ERROR/RECOVERED. Per-service "Alarm Management" controls the channels. Custom HTTP SMS providers (e.g. NetGSM) can be added without code.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 1.6â€“1.7 â€” Reconciliation, descriptions & fixes</p>
                            <ul class="list-disc ml-5 space-y-1.5 mb-3">
                                <li><strong>Reconciliation module:</strong> cross-compares our inventory with the vendor's list (CSV/XLSX), highlighting missing/extra servers and CPU/RAM/Disk/IP/OS mismatches; fully independent and permission-gated.</li>
                                <li><strong>Service description</strong> field shown on dashboard cards, reports and CSV; the chart "Select Service" filter now also applies to the cards.</li>
                                <li><strong>Uptime fix:</strong> CPU/RAM/Disk threshold breaches (ERROR) no longer count as outages in availability reports.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-700 mb-2">Version 1.4â€“1.5 â€” Security hardening & authorization (PCI DSS / ISO 27001 / NIST)</p>
